lleryEnrollmentStatus","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for per-pose prompts; the save signal is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"faceRecognitionTrackerData()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" becoming non-empty once the walk completes.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/yeofr\/yeofrsdk\/begingalleryenrollment(faceid:name:posesequence:lightingphase:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Begin a multi-pose (“gallery”) enrollment with caller-supplied","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"pose targets. The Luxand walk learns each pose’s appearances straight","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"into the tracker as the named face is held in view — identity is the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tracker’s own confidence-gated decision; there is ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"no"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" per-centroid","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"embedding vetting or 0.95 radius-floor on this engine. Capture only the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"intended person: a bystander who steps into the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"frame during the walk can be learned into the gallery.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"externalID":"s:5YEOFR8YEOFRSDKC22beginGalleryEnrollment6faceID4name12poseSequence13lightingPhaseAA15FRSDKReturnCodeOs5Int64V_SSSayAA10PoseTargetOGAA08LightingL6ConfigVtF","roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"beginGalleryEnrollment"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"faceID"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:s5Int64V","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int64"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"name"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"p